==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Accurse
<hw>Ac*curse"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>acursien</ets>, <ets>acorsien</ets>; pref. <ets>a</ets> +
<ets>cursien</ets> to curse. See <er>Curse</er>.]</ety> <def>To devote
to destruction; to imprecate misery or evil upon; to curse; to execrate;
to anathematize.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And the city shall be <qex>accursed</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Josh. vi.
17.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thro' you, my life will be <qex>accurst</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Accurst</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Accursed</ent>⟦br⟧
